@startuml 07-motion-lowering
title Motion Lowering — Semantic Predicates → Compiled Masks

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

component "Semantic Motion\n(dteam-level)" as Motion

component "requires predicates" as Req
component "law predicates" as Law
component "capability predicates" as Cap
component "scenario predicates" as Scen
component "consume predicates" as Cons
component "produce predicates" as Prod

component "prereq mask\n(u64 bits)" as PrereqMask
component "law mask" as LawMask
component "capability mask" as CapMask
component "scenario mask" as ScenMask
component "consume mask" as ConsMask
component "produce mask" as ProdMask

component "Compiled Motion Packet\n(sealed, aligned, typed by tier)" as Packet
component "unios admit\n(denial polarity 0 = admit)" as Admit
component "unibit execute\n(branchless mask kernel)" as Execute
component "ΔU + UReceipt" as Proof

Motion --> Req
Motion --> Law
Motion --> Cap
Motion --> Scen
Motion --> Cons
Motion --> Prod

Req --> PrereqMask
Law --> LawMask
Cap --> CapMask
Scen --> ScenMask
Cons --> ConsMask
Prod --> ProdMask

PrereqMask --> Packet
LawMask --> Packet
CapMask --> Packet
ScenMask --> Packet
ConsMask --> Packet
ProdMask --> Packet

Packet --> Admit
Admit --> Execute
Execute --> Proof

note right of Motion
  dteam reasons in predicates.
  unios lowers to masks.
  unibit executes words.
end note

@enduml
